## Safety (`src/safety/`)
- `safety/mod.rs`
- `safety/diff_validator.rs` — rejects large full-file rewrites
- `safety/intent_validator.rs` — forces clarification on ambiguous edits
- `safety/pre_write_hook.rs` — blocks binaries, massive overwrites
- `safety/suspicious_write_guard.rs` — final dangerous-write checks
- `safety/dry_run.rs` — simulate destructive operations
- `safety/dna_safety.rs` — raises thresholds on repeated failures
- `safety/tool_health_monitor.rs` — per-tool success/failure tracking
- `safety/error.rs`
- `safety/tests.rs`

## Security (`src/security/`)
- `security/mod.rs` — security boundaries and sandboxing
- `security/audit.rs` — audit logging

## Integration
- Hooks into `tools/` (pre-execution checks)
- Used by ACP security and write operations
- Works with Session DNA risk tolerance

## Recent Changes
- More granular safety layers
- DNA-aware safety adjustments
- Stronger tool health monitoring

## Dependencies
- Integrated with tool registry and context engine

## Notes
- Defense-in-depth: multiple layers before any write or shell execution.
- Pre-write hooks and diff validation are especially important for code edits.